It's a quaint art gallery. Very nice to see artists express themselves. I'm sad that no one else was here on a Sunday, especially when entry is free and it's not that time consuming either. Should be more popular!

2 weeks ago i passed by this place when they had an ongoing free exhibition and decided to enter. it was very insightful--some chinese immigrant's watercolour paintings from the previous century were displayed and the exhibition explored the intersection between art and history. great place
